714202f-a.text:
East 67th Street, north side, West from Third Avenue to Central Park (left).  Prominently shown are Ephraim (erected 1890) at 151-5, No 157-9 that houses Fire Engine No 39, Hook and Ladder No 16 and offices of the Board of Education; the 21st Precinct Police Station at No 153,and the New York Neurological Hospital at No 149-151.  Lexington Avenue appears in the left center and all of the aforementioned structures are east of same.

October, 1938

George D chinn
